Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20headaches%20with%20the%20new%20warship%20led%20the%20Navy%20to%20rethink%20how%20it%20does%20Ford-class%20carriers%2C%20but%20those%20early%20first-in-class%20setbacks%20don't%20mean%20the%20Ford%20isn't%20impressive%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20new%20chapter%20for%20aircraft%20carriers%20and%20the%20US%20Navy's%20warship%20capabilities%20and%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20surprising%20the%20Chinese%20would%20develop%20a%20mock-up%20of%20the%20new%20carrier%2C%20Tom%20Shugart%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20submarine%20commander%20who's%20now%20an%20adjunct%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20given%20they%20could%20one%20day%20face%20the%20ship%20in%20a%20potential%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20aircraft%20carrier%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64347fe5ca216e001820fa97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUSS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20on%20March%2019%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FMCS2%20Jackson%20Adkins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20the%20previous%20mock-ups%2C%20the%20targets%20could%20be%20an%20opportunity%20for%20China%20to%20test%20the%20missiles%20of%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Rocket%20Force%20(PLARF)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-doubled-number-missiles-needed-to-target-us-bases-japan-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurther%20develop%20their%20technologies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20potential%20function%20of%20these%20apparent%20targets%2C%20Shugart%20said%2C%20could%20be%20to%20test%20and%20refine%20seekers%20with%20image-recognition%20capabilities%20and%20help%20develop%20a%20missile's%20ability%20to%20accurately%20target%20particular%20ships%20or%20even%20specific%20parts%20of%20ships%20where%20a%20missile%20would%20do%20the%20most%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20purpose%20of%20the%20targets%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20likely%20%26quot%3Bto%20assess%20whether%20the%20target%20recognition%20capabilities%20of%20their%20missile%20seekers%20can%20differentiate%20between%20carriers%20and%20other%20targets%20of%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20Clark%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20officer%20and%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20hypothetical%20war%20scenario%2C%20a%20missile%2C%20traveling%20at%20very%20high%20speeds%20before%20slowing%20down%20upon%20reentry%2C%20would%20only%20have%20a%20short%20time%20to%20find%20its%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20PLA%20wants%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20seeker%20can%20see%20a%20carrier%2C%20discern%20it%20from%20other%20ships%20in%20the%20area%2C%20and%20maneuver%20to%20hit%20it%20within%20only%20a%20few%20seconds%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20the%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20and%20Dwight%20D.%20Eisenhower%20Carrier%20Strike%20Groups%20sail%20together%20in%20the%20Eastern%20Mediterranean.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654564acb788914e5550584c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20and%20Dwight%20D.%20Eisenhower%20Carrier%20Strike%20Groups%20sail%20together%20in%20the%20Eastern%20Mediterranean.%3Cp%3EPetty%20Officer%202nd%20Class%20Jacob%20Mattingly%2FDVIDS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20fake%20warships%20sitting%20out%20in%20the%20desert%2C%20assuming%20the%20intended%20purpose%20is%20targeting%20as%20suspected%2C%20China%20could%20learn%20how%20best%20to%20use%20its%20missiles%20and%20learn%20what%20work%20still%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20threaten%20US%20naval%20forces.%