bringing%20together%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20modeling%20expertise.%20Still%2C%20the%20results%20are%20significantly%20driven%20by%20the%20scenario%20assumptions%2C%20and%20the%20band%20of%20uncertainty%20is%20wide.%20A%20war%20or%20blockade%20of%20shorter%20duration%2C%20and%20with%20less%20significant%20disruptions%20to%20semiconductor%20supply%20and%20trade%2C%20would%20have%20a%20smaller%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Consequential%20Election%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20outcome%20of%20Taiwan's%20election%20doesn't%20trigger%20an%20immediate%20crisis%2C%20it%20will%20define%20the%20direction%20of%20cross-Strait%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELai%20Ching-te%20-%20currently%20serving%20as%20vice%20president%20in%20the%20Democratic%20Progressive%20Party%20administration%20-%20has%20been%20at%20pains%20to%20present%20himself%20as%20a%20continuity%20candidate%2C%20with%20no%20plans%20to%20disturb%20relations%20with%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20though%2C%20he%20described%20himself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpragmatic%20worker%20for%20Taiwanese%20independence.%26quot%3B%20For%20Beijing%2C%20which%20views%20the%20island%20as%20part%20of%20its%20territory%2C%20any%20formal%20push%20for%20independence%20would%20cross%20a%20red%20line.%20At%20his%20meeting%20with%20Biden%2C%20Xi%20expressed%20deep%20concern%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20Lai%20win%2C%20according%20to%20a%20senior%20administration%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DPP%20counterpoint%2C%20which%20aligns%20with%20the%20assessment%20in%20Washington%2C%20is%20that%20Beijing's%20belligerence%20is%20the%20problem%20-%20not%20Taiwan's%20desire%20for%20continued%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELai's%20opponents%20-%20Hou%20Yu-ih%20of%20the%20Kuomintang%20and%20Ko%20Wen-je%20of%20the%20Taiwan%20People's%20Party%20%E2%80%94%20are%20both%20promising%20pragmatic%20steps%20to%20improve%20relations%20with%20Taiwan's%20giant%20neighbor%2C%20without%20sacrificing%20the%20island's%20de%20facto%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20say%20China%20may%20be%20planning%20a%20multipronged%20reaction%20to%20the%20election%2C%20with%20military%20incursions%2C%20economic%20sanctions%20and%20grey%20zone%20tactics%20like%20cyber-attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20Washington%20and%20Taipei%20say%20the%20period%20from%20the%20election%20in%20January%20to%20inauguration%20of%20the%20new%20president%20in%20May%20is%20a%20danger%20zone%20for%20Chinese%20actions%20aimed%20at%20hemming%20in%20Taiwan's%20next%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStraitened%20Circumstances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhoever%20wins%20will%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20changed%2C%20and%20challenging%2C%20set%20of%20cross-Strait%20realities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201979%2C%20when%20the%20US%20switched%20diplomatic%20recognition%20from%20Taipei%20to%20Beijing%2C%20US%20GDP%20was%20ten%20times%20that%20of%20China%2C%20China's%20military%20was%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20modernization%2C%20and%20Taiwan%20was%20still%20under%20single-party%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%20today%20and%20China's%20GDP%20has%20closed%20much%20of%20the%20gap%20with%20the%20US%2C%20its%20military%20boasts%20near-peer%20status%20-%20especially%20close%20to%20home%20-%20and%20Taiwan's%20liberal%20democracy%20is%20a%20visible%20contrast%20to%20China's%20authoritarian%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStatements%20by%20leaders%20in%20Beijing%20and%20Washington%20have%20added%20to%20the%20tension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXi%20has%20said%20more%20than%20once%20that%20Taiwan%20is%20not%20an%20issue%20that%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bpassed%20down%20generation%20after%20generation.%26quot%3B%20Along%20with%20his%20efforts%20to%20modernize%20the%20military%2C%20those%20statements%20have%20spurred%20speculation%20he%20wants%20to%20deliver%20unification%20on%20his%20watch%2C%20with%202027%20cited%20as%20a%20danger%20year%20by%20US%20intelligence%20and%20military%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20his%20meeting%20with%20Biden%2C%20Xi%20vented%20frustration%20with%20the%20view%20that%20China's%20forces%20are%20aiming%20at%20readiness%20for%20an%20invasion%20by%202027%2C%20which%20he%20said%20was%20mistaken%2C%20according%20to%20a%20senior%20US%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fpkngb0og_bloomberg-taiwan-graphic_625x300_11_January_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20Biden%20has%20said%20the%20US%20would%20come%20to%20Taiwan's%20aid%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20Chinese%20invasion.%20That%20bluntness%20eroded%20layers%20of%20carefully%20crafted%20ambiguity%20about%20the%20US%20position%2C%20stoking%20anger%20in%20China%20and%20concerns%20the%20US%20is%20emboldening%20pro-independence%20boisterousness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBloomberg%20Economics'%20Taiwan%20stress%20index%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20warning%20words%20used%20by%20China's%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20and%20military%20incursions%20in%20Taiwan's%20air%20defense%20identification%20zone%20%E2%80%94%20shows%20the%20temperature%20over%20the%20last%20year%20and%20a%20half%20elevated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestors%20and%20businesses%20are%20already%20preparing%20for%20the%20worst.%20Kirk%20Yang%2C%20chairman%20of%20equity%20investment%20fund%20Kirkland%20Capital%20and%20an%20expert%20on%20Asia%20technology%20firms%2C%20says%20the%20fund's%20position%20in%20Taiwan%20is%20now%20close%20to%20zero.%20Geopolitical%20tensions%20have%20%26quot%3Badded%20incentive%20to%20scale%20back%20investments%20at%20a%20faster%20pace%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe's%20in%20good%20company.%20Legendary%20investor%20Warren%20Buffett%20sold%20down%20his%20stake%20in%20TSMC%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20citing%20geopolitical%20risk%20as%20the%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F2isms5fo_investor-bb-graphic_625x300_11_January_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20and%20governments%20are%20also%20making%20preparations.%20Greenfield%20investment%20in%20electronics%20and%20electrical%20equipment%20rocketed%20to%20%24181%20billion%20in%202022%20from%20%2448%20billion%20in%202020%20as%20governments%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%20and%20Germany%20opened%20their%20wallets%20to%20diversify%20sources%20of%20semiconductor%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20an%20upside%20from%20the%20Bloomberg%20Economics%20analysis%2C%20perhaps%20it's%20this%3A%20The%20%2410%20trillion%20cost%20of%20a%20crisis%20would%20be%20so%20high%20for%20all%20players%20that%20the%20incentive%20to%20avoid%20it%20is%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20status%20quo%20might%20be%20no%20one's%20ideal%20outcome%2C%20but%20for%20Taipei%2C%20Beijing%20and%20Washington%20the%20alternatives%20are%20worse.%20That's%20a%20reason%20Taiwan's%20ambiguous%20autonomy%20might%20remain%20an%20equilibrium%20outcome%2C%20even%20as%20the%20conditions%20that%20make%20it%20so%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethodology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFor%20the%20war%20and%20blockade%20scenarios%2C%20Bloomberg%20Economics%20use%20a%20suite%20of%20models%20to%20assess%20the%20impact%20of%20disruptions%20to%20semiconductor%20supply%2C%20trade%20barriers%2C%20and%20financial%20market%20shocks.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESupply%20chain%20disruptions%20are%20assessed%20using%20OECD%20Trade%20in%20Value%20Added%20data%20for%202018.%20OECD%20input-output%20data%20are%20used%20to%20estimate%20the%20direct%20disruptions%20to%20sectors%20using%20semiconductors%20as%20an%20input%20(computer%2C%20electronics%20and%20optical%20products%3B%20electrical%20equipment%3B%20machinery%20and%20equipment%3B%20motor%20vehicles%2C%20trailers%20and%20semi-trailers%3B%20other%20transport%20equipment)%2C%20and%20to%20assess%20the%20spillover%20impact%20onto%20other%20sectors%20-%20for%20example%20the%20impact%20on%20metal%20output%20if%20production%20of%20automobiles%20slows.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETrade%20shocks%20are%20assessed%20using%20the%20WTO%20Global%20Trade%20Model%20(GTM)%20(Aguiar%20et%20al%2C%202019).%20The%20GTM%20is%20a%20recursive%20computational%20general%20equilibrium%20model%20based%20on%20the%20GTAP%20model%20(version%207)%20(Corong%20et%20al%2C%202017).%20We%20shock%20tariffs%20and%20non%20tariff%20measures%2C%20including%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20sanctions%20and%20export%20controls.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUS%20allies%20are%20defined%20based%20on%20trade%20shares%2C%20treaty%20relationships%2C%20and%20Bloomberg%20Economics'%20judgement.%20Australia%2C%20Canada%2C%20the%20European%20Free%20Trade%20Association%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20Japan%2C%20Mexico%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20the%20UK%20are%20defined%20as%20US%20allies.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20shock%20impacts%20are%20estimated%20following%20a%20structural%20approach%20based%20on%20the%20Bayesian%20Global%20VAR%20model%20(Bock%2C%20Feldkircher%20and%20Huber%2C%202020).%20The%20model%20is%20amended%20slightly%20by%20adding%20log%20real%20equity%20prices%20for%20each%20country%20as%20in%20Mohaddes%20and%20Raissi%20(2020).%20Uncertainty%20in%20the%20financial%20markets%20is%20modeled%20as%20a%20global%20shock%20to%20the%20VIX.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20key%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20analysis%20is%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20missing%20semiconductor%20output%20from%20Taiwan%20could%20be%20replaced%20by%20output%20in%20other%20locations%2C%20worked%20around%20by%20manufacturing%20firms%2C%20or%20backstopped%20from%20inventories.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Bloomberg%20Economics%20scenarios%20assume%20that%20all%20production%20using%20semiconductors%20as%20inputs%20has%20to%20be%20reduced%20in%20line%20with%20the%20reduction%20in%20semiconductors%20availability%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E-For%20advanced%20electronics%20such%20as%20smartphones%20using%20cutting-edge%20logic%20chips%2C%20this%20translates%20into%20a%2060%25%20reduction%20in%20production%20in%20the%20blockade%20scenario%2C%20rising%20to%2085%25%20in%20the%20war%20scenario%20when%20access%20to%20South%20Korean%20production%20is%20also%20severely%20curtailed.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn-For%20sectors%20using%20lagging-edge%20logic%20chips%2C%20like%20those%20used%20in%20autos%20and%20home%20electronics%2C%20that%20means%2035%25%20in%20the%20blockade%20scenario%20when%20Taiwan's%20output%20goes%20offline%2C%20and%2062%25%20in%20the%20war%20scenario%20when%20output%20from%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20South%20Korea%20is%20also%20lost.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EReality%20could%20end%20up%20being%20better.%20For%20example%2C%20other%20countries%20could%20amp%20up%20chip%20production%2C%20or%20auto%20firms%20and%20other%20manufacturers%20might%20find%20work%20arounds%20for%20missing%20inputs.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20could%20also%20be%20worse.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20Taiwan's%20chips%20are%20not%20replaceable%20and%20use%20of%20them%20is%20distributed%20widely%20across%20products.%20If%20production%20for%20all%20sectors%20using%20leading%20and%20lagging%20edge%20chips%20goes%20to%20zero%2C%20the%20blow%20to%20global%20GDP%20in%20the%20war%20scenario%20increases%20from%2010.2%25%20to%2014%25.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704972240000%2C%22visual%22